        "body": "I agree for long living services, stdout and stderr files need to be rotated. However, I'm not sure it's good idea to wire them to log, which may mix stdout/stderr output together with log. If some messages are really considered as log, why not writing them directly into log, instead of pushing them to stdout/stderr?",
